  "texts": [
    "This is achieved by replacing most spinlocks with mutexes, which are preemptible, thus reducing latency.",
    "It ensures more predictable task scheduling, meeting the needs of environments where timing and responsiveness are critical, like in robotics, manufacturing, and multimedia applications.To integrate the PREEMPT RT patch into a Linux kernel for enhancing its real-time capabilities, the following steps are undertaken:1.",
    "The source code for the Linux kernel, intended for modification, is acquired from the official Linux kernel archive, ensuring compatibility with the PRE-EMPT RT patch version.2.",
    "The corresponding PREEMPT RT patch is procured from the official PRE-EMPT RT repository, ensuring alignment with the kernel version.3.",
    "The kernel source is extracted, and the PREEMPT RT patch is applied using patching tools provided within the Linux environment."
  ]
}